snippet.textDisplay: Was fiber/hair/DNA evidence tested in '76?? I remember listening to a podcast on the Atlanta Child Murders, and using fiber as evidence was fairly new as of '81. It's possible that the killer cut off the hands because of evidence under her fingernails, but was it tested at the time? Sometimes evidence was collected and stored for future hope that they could test DNA, but I'm not entirely sure the technology was available at the time. It makes me want to research more into the Police Department there at the time and look into the consistency of their forensic practices!
